theorem closure_interior_union_eq_union_closure_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure (interior (A ∪ B : Set X)) =
      closure (interior A) ∪ closure (interior B) := by
  classical
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · intro x hx
    -- Rewrite the set inside the closure using `interior_union`.
    have hx' : x ∈ closure (interior A ∪ interior B) := by
      simpa [interior_union] using hx
    -- Turn the closure of a union into the union of closures.
    have hx'' : x ∈ closure (interior A) ∪ closure (interior B) := by
      simpa [closure_union] using hx'
    exact hx''
  ·
    exact closure_interior_union_subset (A := A) (B := B)

theorem closure_interior_closure_interior_eq
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    closure (interior (closure (interior A))) = closure (interior A) := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  ·
    have h : interior (closure (interior A)) ⊆ closure (interior A) :=
      interior_subset
    exact closure_mono h
  ·
    have h : interior A ⊆ interior (closure (interior A)) := by
      apply interior_mono
      exact (subset_closure : interior A ⊆ closure (interior A))
    exact closure_mono h

theorem interior_diff_subset {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (A \ B : Set X) ⊆ interior A := by
  exact interior_mono (Set.diff_subset)
